:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> The most roguish thing I've ever done happend not too long ago in Crushbone. Some of you will understand the location I am reffering to, some will not...but I'll try to paint a picture for all of you...  <BR>   <BR> It was dusk, shortly after sun down. The air smelt of sulfer and rain from the spells of healing and spells of fire cast this evening. Myself and a small bunch of individuals had managed to hold the throne room against the onslaughts of Orcish renforcements which relentlessly portaled in from Brell knows where. I had loaded up on the leathery bracers the Legonares dropped and was getting ready to leave back for Kelethin, when I heard the sounds of a scrimish outside. I got off my seat on the table and ran to the window. There, clad in leather, was a female wood elf druid with absolutly huge...er ah staff, she had a huge staff and was doing her best to smack the spear-wielding monstrosity of an emmissary off of her. Between the sounds of parrying, grunts and thuds spells were quickly canted and fired off but it was apparant that this was a loosing battle. Without a second to spair, I leaped out the window, rolling to break my fall, landing behind the emmissary. I raised my shiny Stiletto of the Bloodclaw (Pausing to say a quick thanks to Wixramiablo who bestowed it upon me) and slammed it into the broad back of her tormentor. He whirrled around to meet my dirk and stiletto tearing him apart like a froglock on an oger's butcherblock. He quickly turned tail, and after deftly cutting his purse of coins, I finished him off with another dagger in the back. The druid picked up the emmisarys spear, and drove it into the ground next to him, noticed the lack of a purse and grinned at me. She then scampered off into the night, the light of my greater lightstone reflecting off her leather clad butt. What a woman!  <BR>   <BR> Post YOUR most roguish exploits! <p>---------------------<br>
Lindin, Level 18 Monk<br>
Krimzan, Level 16 Rogue<br>
Rodcet Nife</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ukillerbunny.showPublicProfile>KillerBunny</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 10/14/99 6:58:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/13/99 2:27:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> <i> Breaks open a fresh case of JumJum. &quot;Ah, does me whiskers guud to her ya putting such a fine poker to use&quot; barks out the grizzled halfling. &quot;Next, I bee seeing ya in Cazic Thule, I make a fine Lizard Stew, so best bring you napkins and spoons!&quot; <p>Wixramiablo Sneakypants
<i>Souls of Revelance</i>
_________________________
Ring Warden of Rodect Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uflitterbick.showPublicProfile>Flitterbick</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/99 11:43:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> When I had achieved my 40th Dagger of Mastery, I found myself in Lavastorm in need of an infusion of The Wolf to speed my journey to Freeport.  Having spent MANY days in the zone hunting poison components or passing through on my way to Nagafen's Lair, I knew that quite often lower level druids and shaman's fought in front of Najena.    <BR>   <BR> I headed over towards the massive doors signifying the entrance to Najena's dungeon.  Sure enough, I saw a small party of adventurers including what appeared to be a troll shaman.  As I got closer, I noticed that the group was fighting a fire elemental, so i politely waited for them to finish before asking for the blessing.  I informed this party that I would be willing to donate a small sum for their efforts, but I was greeted with stony silence.    <BR>   <BR> Miffed by their rudeness, I changed my offer...  <BR>   <BR> &quot;Ok, could you infuse me with the wolf if I were to give you a bloodstone?&quot;  <BR>   <BR> To this, the troll grumbled &quot;Yes.&quot; and cast the spell upon me.  True to my word, I gave him the bloodstone.  As I turned to go, the troll sent me a belated thanks for the gem I had given him.  My response?...  <BR>   <BR> &quot;No problem.  I pickpocketed it off of the fire elemental you were just fighting.&quot;  <BR>   <BR> :-)  <BR>   <BR> (true story)  <BR>   <BR> Flitterbick Syntadi,  <BR> L46 Rogue, Bristlebane <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uflitterbick.showPublicProfile>Flitterbick</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 10/14/99 7:42:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ulegnanellaf.showPublicProfile>Legna Nellaf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/99 3:28:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> I have no trouble believing you said it. But did you do it? <BR>  <BR> Best thing I have ever done.. <BR>  <BR> Druid is kiting an avo around the karanas.. I am following, picking it, and tossing in a backstab every now and then. <BR>  <BR> The avo falls just after I grab a black pearl. He says thanks. No problem, did it have anything? <BR>  <BR> Nope.  <BR>  <BR> Bummer.. /auction selling black pearl :) <BR>  <BR> -L <p>"Legna, if you are a fighter, how do you backstab?"
"Turn around and I'll show you my secret"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uflitterbick.showPublicProfile>Flitterbick</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/99 4:52:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> My tale was indeed true.  Often times I play EQ at a computer gaming center that a friend of mine owns.  I had at least 8 witnesses.  Half of them cheered me, the other half called me a bastard.   <BR>  <BR> :-) <BR>  <BR> Flitterbick Syntadi <BR> L46 Rogue, Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ukillerbunny.showPublicProfile>KillerBunny</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/99 5:58:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oh I love it!</span><hr size=1> Great stuff Flitterbick! I love it. That story embodies what I think the rogue class should be doing. Same with you Legna. Great stories both of you. <p>---------------------<br>
Lindin, Level 19 Monk<br>
Krimzan, Level 16 Rogue<br>
Rodcet Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uuumirt.showPublicProfile>Uumirt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/31/99 12:04:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cleaning up the dead</span><hr size=1> I was sneaking toward the south gate of Freeport, when all of a sudden the guard was enveloped with a magic cloud.   He began to run into the desert, and naturally, I followed.  He was rooted, nuked, nuked.... etc until dead.  So, when I wander through the area again a minute later I was suprized to see the guard's body still laying there.  Naturally, I looted it.  Nice raw shortsword and a damaged militia helm (short swords sell for 1.5pp, pretty nice at lvl 10).  I did a /who and discovered a lvl 49 DE wizard in the zone.  A brief conversation was struck, during which I discovered that he liked dropping ice comets on the guards.  Fine by me.  The process repeated itself every couple minutes, and so i shortly had a nice collection of raw and bronze short swords.  Some human bard in the zone discovered a guards body while i was waiting for the free loot and decided he was gonna loot it.  After he &quot;stole&quot; that one I determined that I would not be cheated again.  Turns out the loot time is exactly 2 minutes from the time the other person loots the corpse till you get your turn at the left-overs.  I greatly suprized many a passer-by, by appearing at the instant of free loot and stealling &quot;thier&quot; easy corpse.  During  about an hour and a half I made about 15pp on free kills.  This was all well and good for me.  Unfortunately, I made the mistake of PPing a rooted guard during the nuking process.  He uhhh... didnt appreciate it.  Luckily I was bound right next to the secret enterance.  So, from then on I took my easy money and kept my hands to myself.  Also looted three high lvl Necro research items.  All in all a good days wages.  No exp but a $hitload of loot.  For those who disaprove of my actions, I spent my off moment keeping several newbies alive.  Including a couple who were unconcious at the moment of my saving backstab.  Bind wound and here they come again.   <BR>  <BR> I havent adventured enough to have a better story, but this is pretty good for me. <BR>  <BR> Uumirt,  <BR>  <BR> Wanna be Assassin on Tarrew Marr <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> TheWouldBeThief Katzpaw</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/99 6:24:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I am impressed</span><hr size=1> I have only witnessed five levels upon this snow-blighted world we call Norrath.  I have yet to venture farther beyond the snowy confines of my Northern world.  I will soon venture forth once my master deems me suitable for the &quot;outer lands&quot;.  I cannot wait to join my rogue brothers and sisters in their fight against the evil that plagues the land even in my beloved home; merchants.  *winks*  see you somewhere in the shadows or maybe not :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> KardTrick</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/24/99 12:01:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The most Rogueish (sorta) think i've ever done...</span><hr size=1> I was hunting in Nektoulous  (Gotta Love Tallon Zek) with my guild, and i somehow got  <BR> seperated from the small group.  And, then a Dark Elf enchanter fell upon me...she charmed me, but, evidently Bristlebane was watching, and she was attacked by the nearby Halflings.  She could do nothing with me, until the spell had worn off, and i ran.  Unfortunatly, she caught up with me again.  Mesmerized me, and then rooted me...i was standing there, catatonic, defenseless, when i noticed she had sat down...She was going to kill me slowly, <BR> take her time killing me and then brag to her brethren how she had tortured me till I begged  <BR> for death...about this time, the Mesmerization wore off...and although i was still rooted, i remembered something very, very important...She forgot the Fier'Dal's accuracy with a bow...I fire, and she begins to run.  Run!  I became unrooted, and ran back to the Commons.  And, that is the most rogueish think i have ever done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> sinnfein</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/99 7:28:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Most rogueish...</span><hr size=1> Around lvl 12 I think, in BlackBurrow, camping the elite ledge with a warrior. &quot;Hail, a elite guard!&quot; I stand and prepare to backstab when he is zapped by a female Erudite enchanter sans pet from the rock platform below. We follow the gnoll to his prey and watch as he beats the pants off of her. &quot;Can I get a little help here,,,,PLEASE!!!&quot;, says the illusionist. &quot;Should we help her?&quot; asks the warrior. &quot;Sure&quot;, I say, &quot;once you're dead...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/udurden.showPublicProfile>Durden</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/99 4:14:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> I must admit it.  The most roguely thin gI've ever done was ks. <BR>  <BR> I've been down at the aviak tree in SK for the past 3 lvls.  One day I saw a druid, blue to me fighting a named Aviak - which I'd never seen before and yet to see again, which was also blue to me.  I went over and bs'd a couple of times, only thinking I'd help her out while I pp'ed the bird.  I kept coming up empty handed, nothing, I didn't even get 1cp out of this Aviak, so after the Aviak double crushes her for 30's, I stepped in and bs'd that bird to death and got the kill. <BR>  <BR> I looted 1pp and change, Aviak Feathers and a White Pearl.  I didn't find a Lore Item, or a No Drop item.  Anyone know what the feathers are for? <BR>  <BR>  <p>Durden Darkpoint,<BR>
LVL22 Dark Elf Rogue<BR>
Avengers<BR>
Rodcet Nife<BR>
<BR>
"Back up so I can get behind it to backstab.  Oops, I missed.  Taunt it, TAUNT IT,  A LITTLE HELP HERE!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uaalias.showPublicProfile>Aalias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/99 7:00:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> The following event happend one rainy evening in Crushbone as well.  Dissapointed from the people in CB and the way rogue life was working, I was ready to quit playing my rogue until the following happened. <BR>  <BR> Jcwine yelled out to all in the Crushboe camp &quot;Beware those at the entryway to the Greater Faydark.  Ambassador DVinn comes with his minions! All of ye who dare to help take on the foes rally at the tunnel! <BR>  <BR> Dissapointed in the days past events I go to set up camp.  My attempt was broken by an orc cenurion bashing away at my skull with his club. I began to poke at him as hard as I could with my rapier finely crafted of steel and combined with magic.  A fine weapon I must say to have acquired for free at the 14th season.  With a few well placed jabs 'twas dead in a short time.  A massive storm of Orcs all came runing in quickly followed by tons of warriors, clerics, rangers and yes even fellow rogues.  All stood and began to fight everything in sight.  No one in the Crushbone camp had experience for more than 19 seasons of battle.  In time and with a few deaths in the process, most of the orcs were gone with the exceptio of a few Legionairres and Emissaries.  We fought valiantly.  And with the beating I recieved I was worn down to only 75% of my life force remaining. Soon 'twas but DVinn and a few people valiantly trying to kill him.  It dwindled down from 6 to 3. One of them turned and ran passed the in-passable barrier to DVinn and entered the Greater Faydark.  As the warrior trying to go toe to toe with DVinn and his infamous dagger, he dwindles down to somewhat near 20 % of his life remaining before he would be but another corpse for the Orcs to feast upon.  The ranger who was supposed to be aiding fled to the Greater Faydark as well.  The amazing Dark Elf ambassador hammered away the warrior begged &quot;Please young Aalias, help me!&quot;  I rushed over to do what little help I knew I could before I had to flee.  I jabbed my dagger into the center of his back, but he hardly seemed phased and continued assaulting the warrior.  I saw a few shiny platinm sticking out of his pocket and swiped them.  Amazed he turned and looked at me only to give the warrior a chance to flee.  He continued to look at me without moving.  His only action was to put his had up to signal the orc centurions in the area to not interfere.   <BR>    The dark Ambassador spoke to me, &quot;Well young, Aalias I believe you were called.  It appears that you are the only one left.  All others have fled, but you are the only one remaining, cradling the wound you have.  You are no match from me and yet you dare to poke me in the back and seal my money?!?!&quot; <BR>   Trembling, I tried to be bold and replied, &quot; Young I may be, Ambassador.  But you are a mere Dark Elf.  Tunare will watch over me and Bristlebane will guide my Rapier directly to your black heart......through your back!  You as well are wouned and merely half of what you used to be.  I wll send your Dark self to the rock from under which you came!!!&quot; <BR>    He replied, &quot;Fool, now you will see the power of the Dark Elf Brotherhood!!!&quot; <BR>    With that he charged at me with his dagger.  Jabbing constantly trying to hit me.  He missed more times than I can count.  I dodged and bashed at his dagger with my rapier.  I landed  few well placed hits, weak but many in number.  Next came his line of success.  A stab in my shoulder, left torso and leg dropped me to my knees. He jabbed directly at my head but I parried with my rapier and held his dagger against the wall.  I looked him directly in the face and spoke, greatly in pain from his <BR> srength and hits, &quot;You dissapoint me Ambassador.  I would have thought you could at least bring some honor to the Dark Elves.  Is that all you have DVinn?!?!&quot; <BR>      &quot;Foolish wood elf BOY!!  Cunning and quick you may be but you are also weak and puny.  Watch as my dagger tears into your flesh!!!&quot; <BR>      The fighting continued, I dodged, parried and pierced his blue flesh, his blackish blue blood all upon my rapier.  I felt about ready to die but so did he, I could tell.  I landed my rapier straight through his belly.  He looked at me holding his wound and began to slowly limp away unable to run.  Blinded by the blood in his eyes from my pokes at his head, he walked right into a wall, he looked over his shoulder and said, &quot;Fool, my comrades will avenge me.  You shall have all the Indigo Brotherhood on your tail for my death!!!&quot;   <BR>     I thrust my rapier into his back, and directly through his heart.  I withdrew my rapier and on the end of it, his black heart.  His lifeless body fell to the floor.  I leant over and picked up his Dragoon Dirk from his hand, covered in both his blood and mine, I looked at the centurian standing near by.  Amazed, he fled.  I put my rapier in my bag and held the Dragoon Dirk trimphantly in my hand and proceeded back to my hometown to celebrate. <BR>  <BR>   OOC:  This was something that actually happened to me.  I survived the onslaught of orcs and was begged for help by a warrior.  I pick pocketed and DVinn turned to me as the warrior ran.  He atacked and because I didn't really care anymore, we fought with me having 4 bubbles of health and him a bit below 1/2 of his.  The nearby orcs didn't even interfere.  I parried and dodged more than I ever thought I would and landed many more hits than he did.  Eventually he began walking away and walked into a corner where I backstabbed him for the kill.  Looted his black heart and his Dragoon Dirk.  I still have the Dragoon Dirk (now in my offhand) to show for it.  Was truly a great day for my rogue career and led me to continue playig my rogue.  That's my cunning story!!! <p>-~= Aalias, 18th season Scout of Tarew Marr.

"Honestly Guard, I was just showing the guy my Stiletto.  Is it really my fault he turned around and fell onto it?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=parintachin>Parintachin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/99 6:31:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> Well I was venturing into Befallen, hadn't invested in lock picks just yet; and realized I had no key to the first door. <BR> I see this warrior type beating on some Shadow Knight, and mosey on up and pick the Shadow Knights pocket....&quot;Hey!!&quot; got my key....had a grand time too! <BR> The warrior type finished his battle, looted the Shadow Knight and was shouting his confusion, appearantly that Shadow Knight was supposed to have a key......go figure. <BR>  <BR> Parintachin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uunderweird.showPublicProfile>Underweird</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/99 3:20:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> The most roguish thing I've ever done also happened in and around Crushbone Castle.  I was of the 18th circle and my party was of similar experience.  We had fought many battles to secure the throne room and ventured up to the tower where we knew Emperor Crush and DVinn awaited.  However, when we got there a pair of higher level casters camped in the middle of the tower.  They made clear their intention to take every kill.  They were quite rude, in fact.  We decided we could try to outdamage them or leave.  Our party set up camp in the courtyard where the centurions didn't pay us much mind.  I told my group that I would pull Legionaires and disappeared into the castle.  What they didn't know was that I snuck up into the tower unseen.  I waited while the casters threw every spell they had at a preacher.  When the smoke cleared, they sat down to meditate.  DVinn appeared before my very eyes.  While they stared at their spell books, I lept from the shadows, stabbed DVinn in the back and jumped out the window.  DVinn followed me down to the courtyard where my party awaited.  We formed a circle around the sinister dark elf while the casters cried having been wounded by falling.  After chasing DVinn to his corner, one member of our party became the proud owner of a dragoon dirk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kulwaen>Kulwaen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/99 5:35:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> This is great!  I just read this yesterday, and was inspired, so I did a very rogue thing.  I was grouped with four other people in the CB tower, and find that a lvl 50 pally was in the zone.  Varthanos, the pally, graciously buffed my whole group with valor and something else.  Post-buff I had 855hp (got a screenshot to relish in this day).  Of course, we were way over buffed to have 5 people, so one logged, and another left.  Then I was left with a wizzie, a druid (both my level) and Tinlaien.  Tin is a very friendly druid, lvl 36, and was just in the tower (not camping anything, just chillin).  We kicked dvinn around a few times, and the third time (we were rebuffed by same pally) the wizzie got all upset about dvinn hitting him and his 650hp.  We all had a laugh when the wizzie ran away.  But, I was getting bored and wanted more.  We clock the dvinn spawns, so when it got close to time, I asked Tinlaien if we would heal me if I soloed Dvinn.  He agreed.  So I disbanded (was the leader, so the other two were solo as well), right before the spawn and nailed Dvinn.  Even with my 850hp and Tin healing me and hitting Dvinn, my low leveled self got rocked pretty well.  I got the kill, plenty of exp, and a few unhappy ex-group members.  Alas, he didn't have the dirk, but if he did, I would've died like a champ, trying to pull off my most roguish act yet. <p>Kulwaen <br>
Shadow Stalkers
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kriegar</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/14/99 4:17:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most roguish thing I've ever done...</span><hr size=1> The other day I was in Freeport checking out the caster tower (fer the RS that someone mentioned he had found there) when I saw a caster type near one of the merchants beneath the floating tower. I go over to him and there was a bag lying behind him.  Being curious I picked it up but alas it was empty. Shrugging I put it into my inventory. A little bit later I was bored and killing all the green stuff around me near the West Gate while waiting fer me group. Since I was too lazy to go back into town to sell I shouted fer all the newbies to come to the gate fer free stuff.  I noticed among the five who mobbed me that there was the caster I &quot;borrowed&quot; from earlier.  I gave each newbie something (a rat's ear, bat wings, an orc scalp) then it came time fer the caster.  I nonchantly handed him his bag back and walked away.  About one or two minutes later I hear this shout &quot;You damn thieving dwarf!  You stole my bag!&quot;  Guess he finally figured out why I had bent down in front of him earlier. I calmly replied, &quot;No, you are mistaken.  It just looks like one you had.&quot;  He spammed me fer an entire hour after that.  What a loser. <BR>  <BR> Kriegar <BR> Dwarven Rogue <BR> The Tribunal <BR>    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=abalor>Abalor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/00 6:38:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The fine art of deception.</span><hr size=1> I've many a story I could tell ya in my short life time. But here's one some of you more hard hearted might appriciate. (or not) <BR>  <BR> First one started a long while past, a huge barbarian was selling something I'd never before seen, a turtle shell helm. &quot;Hail, My large friend, would you mind if I try this on before I buy, I want to see what it looks like.&quot; <BR>  <BR> &quot;uh, ok, you look like an honest enough guy&quot; <BR>  <BR> &quot;Hey! where'd you go!&quot; <BR>  <BR> To this day I wear the helm, after havin hid and snuck outa there. it's not that great of a helm, offers alittle Str. but it was a clean theft. He called me a few names, &quot;theif among them, hehe, go figure. I told him what he gained was far greater then the gold he could have got, a lesson to never hand a theif your valuables without the money in hand. <BR>  <BR>  <BR>  - - - - - - <BR>  <BR> Next story comes from another witless person, who was standing around Rivervale asking someone to hold his gear so he could twink his new warrior. <BR> &quot;I'll do it&quot; I muttered fromt he shadows. <BR> &quot;Oh, nm, I'll have Abalor do it&quot; he tells the trustworthy Ranger he was talking to. <BR> &quot;a full set of bronze, a Magic shield, and tenticle whip, and 40 plat.&quot; <BR> He logs, I hide, and sneak to saftey. <BR> &quot;Hey! where are you!&quot; <BR> &quot;Fencing some stolen good...&quot; <BR> &quot;oh, where at, I&quot;ll meet you&quot; <BR> &quot;uhh...not mine right?&quot; <BR> :chuckles from the darkness: <BR>  <BR> of course this guy called the GM on me, who got a kick outa it, but made me give most of it back <BR> I later gave the whip to a needy bard gal, so only thing I really got was about 20 plat and the shield (I said I returned MOST) <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uhalen.showPublicProfile>Halen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/00 12:04:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The fine art of deception.</span><hr size=1> I haven't got the heart. I was having some witty chat (*cough*) over /ooc with a paladin in highpass last night, and he gave me an observers staff to pass to a &quot;friend&quot; of his (that he had to log to go get, natch).  I very nearly ran for it at that point... his &quot;friend&quot; gave me 200 plat in return for it, which I gave back to him, cos I'm nice. What did I get in return? Some thanks and a ringmail gloves. Oh the joy... <BR>  <BR> Was playing my shadow knight, not the rogue, but all the same, it was <I>extremely</I> hard not to just log and laugh a lot ;-) <p><P>Halen Sleet, 21st Barbarian Rogue, Bristlebane

